text_1:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
 2.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
 3.The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
 4.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 5.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 6.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
text_2:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.

 2.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
 3.The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
 4.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 5.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 6.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
text_2:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 Iran has its first Supreme Leader: Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.
Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.

 1.Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
 2.Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.
 3.The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
 4.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 5.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.

text_1:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
text_2:

 President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany

The first regular census was conducted by The Zollverein (German Customs Union) in Germany.
USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.

Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany

 1.Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini becomes the first Supreme Leader of Iran.
 2.The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
 3.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 4.Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
 5.Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
text_2:

 3.The Zollverein (German Customs Union) begins the first regular census in Germany
 4.The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
 5.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
